## FAQ

**Q: Can I use FluxMarkdown for free in my company?**  
A: Yes, as long as you comply with GPL-3.0 requirements (i.e., release your modifications as open source under GPL-3.0).

**Q: I'm building a commercial product. Do I need a commercial license?**  
A: Only if you want to keep your derivative work closed-source. If you're willing to open-source your modifications under GPL-3.0, you can use the free license.

**Q: What if I'm just using FluxMarkdown internally without distribution?**  
A: Internal use without distribution is generally covered under GPL-3.0. Contact us if you have specific concerns.

